I have had book marked this restaurant for a while because of the good reviews. First off we lucked out and got a parking spot right in front of the restaurant. If you are not as lucky as I was you will have to park in the lot behind the restaurant and put your money in the pay box. We walk in at 12:30 on a Saturday afternoon and the restaurant is totally packed. We had to wait a few minutes for someone to finish eating and leave. I knew we wanted the black noodles but didn't know which one to order, the waitress suggested the seafood with pork. We also ordered the ground beef sauce. The portions are big and the kimchi and daikon pickles really ad flavor to the dishes. Next time I'm not ordering the beef but will order a side of dumplings. The call it a Northern Chinese restaurant but everyone working there speaks Korean.  I would go back again.
